com.launchdarkly.android.flagstore

Interface FlagInterface

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Flag

    public interface FlagInterface
    Public interface for a Flag, to be used if exposing Flag model to public API methods.

    • Method Detail

      • getKey

        java.lang.String getKey()
        Getter for flag's key
        Returns:
        The flag's key

      • getValue

        com.google.gson.JsonElement getValue()
        Getter for flag's value. The value along with the variation are provided by LaunchDarkly by evaluating full flag rules against the specific user.
        Returns:
        The flag's value

      • getVersion

        java.lang.Integer getVersion()
        Getter for the flag's environment version field. This is an environment global version that is updated whenever any flag is updated in an environment. This field is nullable, as LaunchDarkly may provide only one of version and flagVersion.
        Returns:
        The environment version for this flag

      • getFlagVersion

        java.lang.Integer getFlagVersion()
        Getter for the flag's version. This is a flag specific version that is updated when the specific flag has been updated. This field is nullable, as LaunchDarkly may provide only one of version and flagVersion.
        Returns:
        The flag's version

      • getVariation

        java.lang.Integer getVariation()
        Getter for flag's variation. The variation along with the value are provided by LaunchDarkly by evaluating full flag rules against the specific user.
        Returns:
        The flag's variation

      • getReason

        EvaluationReason getReason()
        Getter for the flag's evaluation reason. The evaluation reason is provided by the server to describe the underlying conditions leading to the selection of the flag's variation and value when evaluated against the particular user.
        Returns:
        The reason describing the flag's evaluation result
